.el .ds Aq '
.TH "daft file merge" 1  "daft file merge " 
.SH NAME
daft file merge \- Merge a source daft.yml into a target daft.yml
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBdaft file merge\fR [\fB\-\-keep\-source\fR] [\fB\-y\fR|\fB\-\-yes\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] <\fIFIRST\fR> [\fISECOND\fR] 
.SH DESCRIPTION
Merge SOURCE into TARGET using the same recursive YAML merge that daft uses
at load time: source wins on conflicts, new hook sections are added wholesale.
.PP
When TARGET is omitted, daft.yml in the current directory is used.
.PP
By default the source file is deleted after a successful merge.
When TARGET is untracked (visitor file) you are prompted for confirmation
unless \-\-yes / \-\-force is passed.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-keep\-source\fR
Keep the source file after merging (do not delete it)
.TP
\fB\-y\fR, \fB\-\-yes\fR
Skip confirmation prompt when the target is untracked
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help (see a summary with \*(Aq\-h\*(Aq)
.TP
<\fIFIRST\fR>
Target file to merge INTO, or source file when TARGET is omitted
.TP
[\fISECOND\fR]
Source file to merge FROM (optional; when omitted, FIRST is the source and the target defaults to daft.yml in the current directory)
